# Day 85: Integration Testing with MockMvc

**Topics Covered:**
1. What is `MockMvc`? (Simulating HTTP requests).
2. `@WebMvcTest` annotation.
3. Testing Endpoints (`GET`, `POST`).
4. Checking Status Codes and Response Body.

**Learning Summary:**
How do we test Controllers? We can't easily start the server for every test. Today I learned about `MockMvc`. It allows us to send fake HTTP requests to our controllers and assert the response. I tested if my `/hello` endpoint returns status 200 and the correct message.

**Code Snippet:**
```java
@WebMvcTest(UserController.class)
class UserControllerTest {

    @Autowired
    private MockMvc mockMvc;

    @MockBean
    private UserService service; // Mocking the service layer

    @Test
    void testGetUser() throws Exception {
        // Prepare data
        User user = new User("Amit", "Dev");
        when(service.getUserById(1)).thenReturn(user);

        // Perform GET Request
        mockMvc.perform(get("/users/1"))
                .andExpect(status().isOk()) // Expect 200 OK
                .andExpect(jsonPath("$.name").value("Amit")); // Check JSON content
    }
}
